sec.p:
This approach is based on the following stages:


using the simple rule of mixtures to obtain the ultimate tensile strength of a composite containing short fibers parallel to the applied load (σc);

considering the failure criteria for laminated composites and evaluating the tensile strength of a composite with parallel fibers which are placed at an inclined angle, θ, to the applied load (σusc);

integrating the obtained equation for tensile strength of the off-axis unidirectional fiber-reinforced composites with respect to θ to evaluate the tensile strength of randomly oriented fiber-reinforced composites (σ Random).
